{"ts": "2026-06-12T10:09:13.000Z", "event": "planner", "msg": "L3 task decomposition", "agent": "planner-l3", "tokens_in": 1782, "tokens_out": 17969, "elapsed_ms": 236960, "model": "deepseek-v4-pro", "prompt": "You are the Level 3 Planner. Decompose the user task into subtasks for dynamic agent creation.\n\nOutput JSON:\n{{\n  \"subtasks\": [\n    {{\"task_id\": \"short-name\", \"description\": \"What this worker must produce — ALWAYS include the user's exact request at the top\"}}\n  ]\n}}\n\n## Critical Rules\n- Each subtask description MUST begin with \"USER REQUEST: <exact user task text>\" — this prevents worker hallucination\n- Each subtask must be focused, self-contained, with explicit output file names\n- Never create duplicate task_ids — each worker name must be unique\n- For simple tasks, 3-4 subtasks; for complex tasks, 4-6\n- Always include a \"tester\" as the FINAL subtask — running test_report.json validation\n- Specify exact file names each worker must produce (e.g. \"Write to styles.css\", \"Write to app.js\")\n- Workers receive NO prior context beyond their subtask description — be thorough in the description\n- Output ONLY the JSON object — no markdown fences, no extra text\n\n## Specialty\nfrontend\n\n## User Request\nBuild a single-page SaaS dashboard landing page with dark/light theme and scroll-triggered section animations. Deliver ONLY: index.html, styles.css, app.js.\n\n## 1. THEME SYSTEM (dark mode toggle)\n- Navbar has a sun/moon emoji button that toggles between dark and light themes\n- Dark theme: body background #0f172a, text #e2e8f0, cards #1e293b\n- Light theme: body background #ffffff, text #1e293b, cards #f8fafc\n- Add a data-theme=\"dark\" or data-theme=\"light\" attribute on <html> via JavaScript\n- Store the user's choice in localStorage; on page reload, restore the saved theme\n- Default to dark theme on first visit\n- ALL color changes must use CSS transition: background-color 0.3s, color 0.3s\n\n## 2. SCROLL ANIMATIONS (CSS + IntersectionObserver)\n- Each major <section> starts hidden (opacity: 0, transform: translateY(40px))\n- When a section scrolls into view (IntersectionObserver at 15% threshold), add class 'visible' which triggers: opacity: 1; transform: translateY(0); transition: all 0.6s ease-out\n- Sections should animate in staggered — each section appears as the user scrolls to it\n- Hero section animates immediately on page load (no scroll needed)\n\n## 3. PAGE SECTIONS (top to bottom)\n### Navbar (sticky)\n- Logo text \"Dashflow\" on the left\n- 4 nav links: Features, Stats, Pricing, Contact (smooth scroll to section IDs)\n- Theme toggle button (sun/moon) on the right\n- Sticks to top when scrolling (position: sticky)\n\n### Hero\n- Large headline \"Powerful Analytics for Modern Teams\"\n- Subheadline \"Track metrics, gain insights, and grow faster with real-time data.\"\n- CTA button \"Get Started Free\" with a subtle CSS pulse animation (scale 1->1.03->1 every 2s)\n- Animated gradient background: linear-gradient that slowly shifts hues using CSS @keyframes\n\n### Features (3 cards)\n- Card 1: icon (bar-chart emoji), title \"Real-Time Analytics\", description about live dashboards\n- Card 2: icon (shield emoji), title \"Enterprise Security\", description about data protection\n- Card 3: icon (lightning emoji), title \"Lightning Fast\", description about performance\n- Cards have hover lift effect: transform: translateY(-4px); box-shadow increase; transition 0.2s\n\n### Stats Bar (4 counters)\n- Projects: 12,500+ — Users: 8,200+ — Uptime: 99.9% — Awards: 24\n- Each counter animates from 0 to target when the stats section scrolls into view\n- Use IntersectionObserver + requestAnimationFrame for smooth counting\n- Numbers should have a subtle scale-pop when reaching their target\n\n### Testimonials (carousel)\n- 3 testimonial cards: quote text, person name, role\n- Prev/Next buttons and 3 dot indicators below\n- Clicking a dot or button shows that testimonial with a fade transition\n- Auto-advance every 5 seconds, but pause when user hovers the carousel\n\n### Pricing (3 tiers)\n- Starter: $9/mo — Pro (recommended): $29/mo — Enterprise: $99/mo\n- Pro card should have a highlighted border and \"Most Popular\" badge\n- Cards have equal height and center-align\n- Hover: slight scale(1.02) with box-shadow increase\n\n### Newsletter + Footer\n- Email input + Subscribe button\n- Validate email format on submit (regex check for @ and .)\n- Invalid email: show red border + shake animation (CSS @keyframes horizontal shake)\n- Valid email: clear input, show green \"Subscribed!\" toast notification that fades out after 3s\n- Footer: copyright, 3 columns of placeholder links, social media icon placeholders (emoji)\n\n## 4. RESPONSIVE DESIGN\n- Mobile (375px): single column, hamburger menu (animated slide from right), stacked cards\n- Tablet (768px): 2-column features, stats in 2x2 grid\n- Desktop (1280px+): 3-column features, stats in a row, full navbar\n- Use CSS Grid + Flexbox, media queries at 768px and 1024px\n\n## 5. CRITICAL RULES\n- Everything in ONE index.html file with linked styles.css and app.js\n- ALL CSS classes must have semantic names matching their section (class=\"hero\", class=\"features\", class=\"stats\", class=\"testimonials\", class=\"pricing\", class=\"newsletter\")\n- JavaScript MUST reference real DOM elements that exist in the HTML\n- The theme toggle MUST actually change the visual appearance — test both themes\n- Do NOT use any external libraries, CDNs, or frameworks — pure HTML/CSS/JS only\n\nFor frontend tasks, you MUST follow these constraints:\n- Always include a final \"integration\" subtask that merges all content/fragments into index.html\n- Always include a \"tester\" subtask as the VERY LAST subtask\n- Good decomposition: [content, html_structure, styling, interactivity, integration, tester]\n- Bad decomposition: [hero_builder, features_builder, cta_builder] — these create standalone pages\n- Each subtask description MUST include the user's verbatim request text at the top\n- Section subtasks produce content fragments into shared files, NOT standalone HTML files\n- The pipeline produces ONE web page: index.html + styles.css + app.js\n\n## CSS-HTML Coordination\n- The HTML worker MUST add semantic CSS classes to every major section (class=\"hero\", class=\"features\", class=\"cta\", class=\"footer\" etc.)\n- The styling worker's subtask MUST say: \"read_file('index.html') FIRST. Write CSS selectors matching the EXACT classes/IDs/elements found in index.html. Do NOT invent new class names.\"\n- The integration subtask MUST include: \"1) read index.html to see classes used, 2) read content.txt for real text, 3) read styles.css to see which classes need to exist, 4) write_file('index.html') with content injected AND missing CSS classes added, 5) read_file('index.html') to verify.\"\n\n## Token Efficiency\n- Each worker≈100K token budget limit for the entire pipeline, plan your decomposition and worker complexity accordingly\n- Avoid micro-workers that do trivial tasks — combine related work into fewer, more substantial workers\n- The CSS/styling worker should NOT call validate_css more than 3 times total", "meta": {}}
{"ts": "2026-06-12T10:11:12.000Z", "event": "agent_creator", "msg": "Agent Creator L3 — generating workers", "agent": "agent-creator-l3", "tokens_in": 9701, "tokens_out": 7193, "elapsed_ms": 119507, "model": "deepseek-v4-pro", "prompt": "You are the Advanced Agent Creator (Level 3 — Fully Autonomous). Your role: create worker agents from scratch with custom system instructions, tools, and dynamic code tools.\n\n## Available Tools\nThe tool menu for this specialty:\n[\"read_file\", \"write_file\", \"list_files\", \"run_command\", \"render_html_screenshot\", \"render_html_file_screenshot\", \"validate_html\", \"validate_css\", \"read_image\", \"generate_image\"]\n\n## Task Plan\nThe planner has decomposed the task into subtasks:\n{\n  \"subtasks\": [\n    {\n      \"task_id\": \"html_structure\",\n      \"description\": \"USER REQUEST: Build a single-page SaaS dashboard landing page with dark/light theme and scroll-triggered section animations. Deliver ONLY: index.html, styles.css, app.js.\\n\\n## 1. THEME SYSTEM (dark mode toggle)\\n- Navbar has a sun/moon emoji button that toggles between dark and light themes\\n- Dark theme: body background #0f172a, text #e2e8f0, cards #1e293b\\n- Light theme: body background #ffffff, text #1e293b, cards #f8fafc\\n- Add a data-theme=\\\"dark\\\" or data-theme=\\\"light\\\" attribute on <html> via JavaScript\\n- Store the user's choice in localStorage; on page reload, restore the saved theme\\n- Default to dark theme on first visit\\n- ALL color changes must use CSS transition: background-color 0.3s, color 0.3s\\n\\n## 2. SCROLL ANIMATIONS (CSS + IntersectionObserver)\\n- Each major <section> starts hidden (opacity: 0, transform: translateY(40px))\\n- When a section scrolls into view (IntersectionObserver at 15% threshold), add class 'visible' which triggers: opacity: 1; transform: translateY(0); transition: all 0.6s ease-out\\n- Sections should animate in staggered \\u2014 each section appears as the user scrolls to it\\n- Hero section animates immediately on page load (no scroll needed)\\n\\n## 3. PAGE SECTIONS (top to bottom)\\n### Navbar (sticky)\\n- Logo text \\\"Dashflow\\\" on the left\\n- 4 nav links: Features, Stats, Pricing, Contact (smooth scroll to section IDs)\\n- Theme toggle button (sun/moon) on the right\\n- Sticks to top when scrolling (position: sticky)\\n\\n### Hero\\n- Large headline \\\"Powerful Analytics for Modern Teams\\\"\\n- Subheadline \\\"Track metrics, gain insights, and grow faster with real-time data.\\\"\\n- CTA button \\\"Get Started Free\\\" with a subtle CSS pulse animation (scale 1->1.03->1 every 2s)\\n- Animated gradient background: linear-gradient that slowly shifts hues using CSS @keyframes\\n\\n### Features (3 cards)\\n- Card 1: icon (bar-chart emoji), title \\\"Real-Time Analytics\\\", description about live dashboards\\n- Card 2: icon (shield emoji), title \\\"Enterprise Security\\\", description about data protection\\n- Card 3: icon (lightning emoji), title \\\"Lightning Fast\\\", description about performance\\n- Cards have hover lift effect: transform: translateY(-4px); box-shadow increase; transition 0.2s\\n\\n### Stats Bar (4 counters)\\n- Projects: 12,500+ \\u2014 Users: 8,200+ \\u2014 Uptime: 99.9% \\u2014 Awards: 24\\n- Each counter animates from 0 to target when the stats section scrolls into view\\n- Use IntersectionObserver + requestAnimationFrame for smooth counting\\n- Numbers should have a subtle scale-pop when reaching their target\\n\\n### Testimonials (carousel)\\n- 3 testimonial cards: quote text, person name, role\\n- Prev/Next buttons and 3 dot indicators below\\n- Clicking a dot or button shows that testimonial with a fade transition\\n- Auto-advance every 5 seconds, but pause when user hovers the carousel\\n\\n### Pricing (3 tiers)\\n- Starter: $9/mo \\u2014 Pro (recommended): $29/mo \\u2014 Enterprise: $99/mo\\n- Pro card should have a highlighted border and \\\"Most Popular\\\" badge\\n- Cards have equal height and center-align\\n- Hover: slight scale(1.02) with box-shadow increase\\n\\n### Newsletter + Footer\\n- Email input + Subscribe button\\n- Validate email format on submit (regex check for @ and .)\\n- Invalid email: show red border + shake animation (CSS @keyframes horizontal shake)\\n- Valid email: clear input, show green \\\"Subscribed!\\\" toast notification that fades out after 3s\\n- Footer: copyright, 3 columns of placeholder links, social media icon placeholders (emoji)\\n\\n## 4. RESPONSIVE DESIGN\\n- Mobile (375px): single column, hamburger menu (animated slide from right), stacked cards\\n- Tablet (768px): 2-column features, stats in 2x2 grid\\n- Desktop (1280px+): 3-column features, stats in a row, full navbar\\n- Use CSS Grid + Flexbox, media queries at 768px and 1024px\\n\\n## 5. CRITICAL RULES\\n- Everything in ONE index.html file with linked styles.css and app.js\\n- ALL CSS classes must have semantic names matching their section (class=\\\"hero\\\", class=\\\"features\\\", class=\\\"stats\\\", class=\\\"testimonials\\\", class=\\\"pricing\\\", class=\\\"newsletter\\\")\\n- JavaScript MUST reference real DOM elements that exist in the HTML\\n- The theme toggle MUST actually change the visual appearance \\u2014 test both themes\\n- Do NOT use any external libraries, CDNs, or frameworks \\u2014 pure HTML/CSS/JS only\\n\\n---\\n\\nCreate the initial index.html file. It must contain the complete HTML5 boilerplate, including <!DOCTYPE html>, <html> with data-theme attribute initially set to 'dark' (but will be managed by JS). In the <head>, set meta charset, viewport, title 'Dashflow - SaaS Dashboard', and link to styles.css and defer script to app.js. Construct the body with all the required sections using semantic HTML5 tags (<nav>, <section>, <footer>, etc.) and assign classes exactly as specified: class='navbar', class='hero', class='features', class='stats', class='testimonials', class='pricing', class='newsletter', class='footer'. Each section must have an id for smooth scrolling (e.g., id='features'). The navbar must include a logo 'Dashflow', nav links with href='#features', '#stats', '#pricing', '#contact', and a theme toggle button with sun/moon emoji and appropriate class. The hero section must have the headline, subheadline, and CTA button. Features section must have three cards with emoji icons, titles, and descriptions (use placeholder text for descriptions: 'Lorem ipsum...' or actual brief text). Stats bar with four counters arranged in a grid/row, each with a data-target attribute for JS counting (e.g., data-target='12500'). Testimonials section with three cards, each with quote, name, role; also include prev/next buttons and dot indicators. Pricing section with three cards, the Pro card having a 'popular' badge. Newsletter section with email input and subscribe button, and a container for toast notification. Footer with copyright, three columns of links (use placeholder text), and social emojis. For mobile, include a hamburger button (hidden on desktop) and a mobile nav menu that will be controlled by JS. Use placeholder emojis for icons. Ensure all elements are properly structured so that CSS and JS can target them. Output only the index.html file content.\"\n    },\n    {\n      \"task_id\": \"css_styling\",\n      \"description\": \"USER REQUEST: Build a single-page SaaS dashboard landing page with dark/light theme and scroll-triggered section animations. Deliver ONLY: index.html, styles.css, app.js.\\n\\n## 1. THEME SYSTEM (dark mode toggle)\\n- Navbar has a sun/moon emoji button that toggles between dark and light themes\\n- Dark theme: body background #0f172a, text #e2e8f0, cards #1e293b\\n- Light theme: body background #ffffff, text #1e293b, cards #f8fafc\\n- Add a data-theme=\\\"dark\\\" or data-theme=\\\"light\\\" attribute on <html> via JavaScript\\n- Store the user's choice in localStorage; on page reload, restore the saved theme\\n- Default to dark theme on first visit\\n- ALL color changes must use CSS transition: background-color 0.3s, color 0.3s\\n\\n## 2. SCROLL ANIMATIONS (CSS + IntersectionObserver)\\n- Each major <section> starts hidden (opacity: 0, transform: translateY(40px))\\n- When a section scrolls into view (IntersectionObserver at 15% threshold), add class 'visible' which triggers: opacity: 1; transform: translateY(0); transition: all 0.6s ease-out\\n- Sections should animate in staggered \\u2014 each section appears as the user scrolls to it\\n- Hero section animates immediately on page load (no scroll needed)\\n\\n## 3. PAGE SECTIONS (top to bottom)\\n### Navbar (sticky)\\n- Logo text \\\"Dashflow\\\" on the left\\n- 4 nav links: Features, Stats, Pricing, Contact (smooth scroll to section IDs)\\n- Theme toggle button (sun/moon) on the right\\n- Sticks to top when scrolling (position: sticky)\\n\\n### Hero\\n- Large headline \\\"Powerful Analytics for Modern Teams\\\"\\n- Subheadline \\\"Track metrics, gain insights, and grow faster with real-time data.\\\"\\n- CTA button \\\"Get Started Free\\\" with a subtle CSS pulse animation (scale 1->1.03->1 every 2s)\\n- Animated gradient background: linear-gradient that slowly shifts hues using CSS @keyframes\\n\\n### Features (3 cards)\\n- Card 1: icon (bar-chart emoji), title \\\"Real-Time Analytics\\\", description about live dashboards\\n- Card 2: icon (shield emoji), title \\\"Enterprise Security\\\", description about data protection\\n- Card 3: icon (lightning emoji), title \\\"Lightning Fast\\\", description about performance\\n- Cards have hover lift effect: transform: translateY(-4px); box-shadow increase; transition 0.2s\\n\\n### Stats Bar (4 counters)\\n- Projects: 12,500+ \\u2014 Users: 8,200+ \\u2014 Uptime: 99.9% \\u2014 Awards: 24\\n- Each counter animates from 0 to target when the stats section scrolls into view\\n- Use IntersectionObserver + requestAnimationFrame for smooth counting\\n- Numbers should have a subtle scale-pop when reaching their target\\n\\n### Testimonials (carousel)\\n- 3 testimonial cards: quote text, person name, role\\n- Prev/Next buttons and 3 dot indicators below\\n- Clicking a dot or button shows that testimonial with a fade transition\\n- Auto-advance every 5 seconds, but pause when user hovers the carousel\\n\\n### Pricing (3 tiers)\\n- Starter: $9/mo \\u2014 Pro (recommended): $29/mo \\u2014 Enterprise: $99/mo\\n- Pro card should have a highlighted border and \\\"Most Popular\\\" badge\\n- Cards have equal height and center-align\\n- Hover: slight scale(1.02) with box-shadow increase\\n\\n### Newsletter + Footer\\n- Email input + Subscribe button\\n- Validate email format on submit (regex check for @ and .)\\n- Invalid email: show red border + shake animation (CSS @keyframes horizontal shake)\\n- Valid email: clear input, show green \\\"Subscribed!\\\" toast notification that fades out after 3s\\n- Footer: copyright, 3 columns of placeholder links, social media icon placeholders (emoji)\\n\\n## 4. RESPONSIVE DESIGN\\n- Mobile (375px): single column, hamburger menu (animated slide from right), stacked cards\\n- Tablet (768px): 2-column features, stats in 2x2 grid\\n- Desktop (1280px+): 3-column features, stats in a row, full navbar\\n- Use CSS Grid + Flexbox, media queries at 768px and 1024px\\n\\n## 5. CRITICAL RULES\\n- Everything in ONE index.html file with linked styles.css and app.js\\n- ALL CSS classes must have semantic names matching their section (class=\\\"hero\\\", class=\\\"features\\\", class=\\\"stats\\\", class=\\\"testimonials\\\", class=\\\"pricing\\\", class=\\\"newsletter\\\")\\n- JavaScript MUST reference real DOM elements that exist in the HTML\\n- The theme toggle MUST actually change the visual appearance \\u2014 test both themes\\n- Do NOT use any external libraries, CDNs, or frameworks \\u2014 pure HTML/CSS/JS only\\n\\n---\\n\\nFirst, read_file('index.html') to inspect the HTML structure, class names, and IDs. This is critical: your CSS selectors must exactly match the elements found in the HTML. Then write styles.css. Implement the following:\\n\\n- Global reset and base styles (box-sizing, margin, padding).\\n- Theme system: Use [data-theme='dark'] and [data-theme='light'] selectors on the html element to define CSS custom properties (variables) for colors: background, text, card background, etc. Alternatively, use a class-based approach but must respect the data-theme attribute as per spec. Define dark theme colors: body bg #0f172a, text #e2e8f0, cards #1e293b. Light theme: body bg #fff, text #1e293b, cards #f8fafc. Set transitions on body, cards, etc for background-color 0.3s, color 0.3s.\\n- Navbar: sticky top, flex, logo left, links center, toggle right; hover effects. Mobile hamburger menu styles (animated slide from right, use transform/translateX).\\n- Hero: large text, gradient background animated with @keyframes (shifting hues), CTA button with pulse animation (scale 1->1.03->1 every 2s using @keyframes pulse). Ensure hero is visible immediately (no initial hidden unless for animation).\\n- Features: 3 cards layout (grid), card styles with hover lift effect (translateY(-4px), box-shadow increase, transition 0.2s). Emoji icons styled appropriately.\\n- Stats: grid/flex layout, counter number styling.\\n- Testimonials: carousel styling, cards center, fade transition (opacity transition for showing/hiding), dot indicators active state, prev/next buttons.\\n- Pricing: 3 cards equal height, center-aligned, Pro card highlighted border and a badge. Hover scale(1.02) with box-shadow.\\n- Newsletter: input and button styling; invalid state (red border) and shake animation @keyframes shake; valid state styling; toast notification (green background, fade out animation after 3s).\\n- Footer: dark background, columns, social emoji links.\\n- Scroll animations: All major sections (except hero) should have default opacity: 0, transform: translateY(40px) (or use a class like .animate-on-scroll). When they have the .visible class, they become opacity: 1, transform: translateY(0), transition all 0.6s ease-out. However, since JS will add the .visible class, you must define these styles. The hero section can be immediately visible, but you can still add a class for consistency.\\n- Responsive media queries: at 768px, adjust grid for features 2-column, stats 2x2, etc. At 1024px, adjust for desktop 3-column features, stats row. Mobile 375px: single column, hamburger menu visible, stacked everything. Ensure navbar collapses.\\n- Import a sans-serif font like system font stack.\\n\\nDo NOT use any external libraries. Use only CSS. Write the complete styles.css file.\"\n    },\n    {\n      \"task_id\": \"js_interactivity\",\n      \"description\": \"USER REQUEST: Build a single-page SaaS dashboard landing page with dark/light theme and scroll-triggered section animations. Deliver ONLY: index.html, styles.css, app.js.\\n\\n## 1. THEME SYSTEM (dark mode toggle)\\n- Navbar has a sun/moon emoji button that toggles between dark and light themes\\n- Dark theme: body background #0f172a, text #e2e8f0, cards #1e293b\\n- Light theme: body background #ffffff, text #1e293b, cards #f8fafc\\n- Add a data-theme=\\\"dark\\\" or data-theme=\\\"light\\\" attribute on <html> via JavaScript\\n- Store the user's choice in localStorage; on page reload, restore the saved theme\\n- Default to dark theme on first visit\\n- ALL color changes must use CSS transition: background-color 0.3s, color 0.3s\\n\\n## 2. SCROLL ANIMATIONS (CSS + IntersectionObserver)\\n- Each major <section> starts hidden (opacity: 0, transform: translateY(40px))\\n- When a section scrolls into view (IntersectionObserver at 15% threshold), add class 'visible' which triggers: opacity: 1; transform: translateY(0); transition: all 0.6s ease-out\\n- Sections should animate in staggered \\u2014 each section appears as the user scrolls to it\\n- Hero section animates immediately on page load (no scroll needed)\\n\\n## 3. PAGE SECTIONS (top to bottom)\\n### Navbar (sticky)\\n- Logo text \\\"Dashflow\\\" on the left\\n- 4 nav links: Features, Stats, Pricing, Contact (smooth scroll to section IDs)\\n- Theme toggle button (sun/moon) on the right\\n- Sticks to top when scrolling (position: sticky)\\n\\n### Hero\\n- Large headline \\\"Powerful Analytics for Modern Teams\\\"\\n- Subheadline \\\"Track metrics, gain insights, and grow faster with real-time data.\\\"\\n- CTA button \\\"Get Started Free\\\" with a subtle CSS pulse animation (scale 1->1.03->1 every 2s)\\n- Animated gradient background: linear-gradient that slowly shifts hues using CSS @keyframes\\n\\n### Features (3 cards)\\n- Card 1: icon (bar-chart emoji), title \\\"Real-Time Analytics\\\", description about live dashboards\\n- Card 2: icon (shield emoji), title \\\"Enterprise Security\\\", description about data protection\\n- Card 3: icon (lightning emoji), title \\\"Lightning Fast\\\", description about performance\\n- Cards have hover lift effect: transform: translateY(-4px); box-shadow increase; transition 0.2s\\n\\n### Stats Bar (4 counters)\\n- Projects: 12,500+ \\u2014 Users: 8,200+ \\u2014 Uptime: 99.9% \\u2014 Awards: 24\\n- Each counter animates from 0 to target when the stats section scrolls into view\\n- Use IntersectionObserver + requestAnimationFrame for smooth counting\\n- Numbers should have a subtle scale-pop when reaching their target\\n\\n### Testimonials (carousel)\\n- 3 testimonial cards: quote text, person name, role\\n- Prev/Next buttons and 3 dot indicators below\\n- Clicking a dot or button shows that testimonial with a fade transition\\n- Auto-advance every 5 seconds, but pause when user hovers the carousel\\n\\n### Pricing (3 tiers)\\n- Starter: $9/mo \\u2014 Pro (recommended): $29/mo \\u2014 Enterprise: $99/mo\\n- Pro card should have a highlighted border and \\\"Most Popular\\\" badge\\n- Cards have equal height and center-align\\n- Hover: slight scale(1.02) with box-shadow increase\\n\\n### Newsletter + Footer\\n- Email input + Subscribe button\\n- Validate email format on submit (regex check for @ and .)\\n- Invalid email: show red border + shake animation (CSS @keyframes horizontal shake)\\n- Valid email: clear input, show green \\\"Subscribed!\\\" toast notification that fades out after 3s\\n- Footer: copyright, 3 columns of placeholder links, social media icon placeholders (emoji)\\n\\n## 4. RESPONSIVE DESIGN\\n- Mobile (375px): single column, hamburger menu (animated slide from right), stacked cards\\n- Tablet (768px): 2-column features, stats in 2x2 grid\\n- Desktop (1280px+): 3-column features, stats in a row, full navbar\\n- Use CSS Grid + Flexbox, media queries at 768px and 1024px\\n\\n## 5. CRITICAL RULES\\n- Everything in ONE index.html file with linked styles.css and app.js\\n- ALL CSS classes must have semantic names matching their section (class=\\\"hero\\\", class=\\\"features\\\", class=\\\"stats\\\", class=\\\"testimonials\\\", class=\\\"pricing\\\", class=\\\"newsletter\\\")\\n- JavaScript MUST reference real DOM elements that exist in the HTML\\n- The theme toggle MUST actually change the visual appearance \\u2014 test both themes\\n- Do NOT use any external libraries, CDNs, or frameworks \\u2014 pure HTML/CSS/JS only\\n\\n---\\n\\nFirst, read_file('index.html') to understand the DOM structure, class names, IDs, and data attributes. This is critical: your JavaScript selectors must match real elements. Then write app.js. Implement the following with vanilla JS:\\n\\n- Theme Toggle: On page load, check localStorage for 'theme' value and apply it by setting document.documentElement.setAttribute('data-theme', theme) and updating the toggle button emoji (sun/moon). Default to 'dark' if not set. On button click, toggle theme, update localStorage, update attribute, and change emoji. Use event listener.\\n- Smooth scrolling for nav links: add click listeners to all anchor links with href starting with '#', prevent default, and use element.scrollIntoView({ behavior: 'smooth' }).\\n- Scroll Animations: Use IntersectionObserver with threshold 0.15. Observe all major <section> elements (maybe select by a common class like .scroll-section). When intersecting, add class 'visible' to trigger CSS transition. For the hero, immediately add 'visible' on DOMContentLoaded so it appears without scroll. Ensure staggered effect is handled by CSS transition delays or by the natural reveal as they enter viewport; you can assign transition-delay in CSS or just let the observer trigger sequentially.\\n- Stats Counter Animation: Select the stats section and set up an IntersectionObserver to trigger counting when it enters viewport. For each counter element, get the data-target attribute, and use requestAnimationFrame to increment from 0 to target over ~2 seconds. Use easing or simple steps. Add a scale-pop effect at the end by adding a CSS class briefly.\\n- Testimonials Carousel: Track current index. Show only the active card (others hidden or with opacity 0). Implement prev/next buttons to cycle through testimonials. Also dot indicators that highlight the active dot and allow clicking. Add auto-advance every 5 seconds using setInterval, but clearInterval on mouseenter and restart on mouseleave. Use fade transition by toggling a class.\\n- Newsletter Form Validation: On submit, prevent default. Get input value, validate with regex that checks for '@' and '.' (simple). If invalid, add a class to input for red border and apply shake animation (add/remove class to trigger animation), and prevent submission. If valid, clear input, show toast notification with green \\\"Subscribed!\\\" text, and fade it out after 3 seconds (setTimeout to remove toast or hide). Implement toast container as a div that becomes visible and then hides.\\n- Mobile Hamburger Menu: On hamburger click, toggle a class on the mobile nav menu to slide it in/out. Also close menu when a nav link is clicked.\\n- Ensure all code is wrapped in DOMContentLoaded or placed at end of body (with defer script). Use 'strict' mode maybe.\\n- Store no variables in global scope more than necessary (use an IIFE or just functions).\\n- Test that all DOM queries are valid by cross-referencing with the HTML you read.\\n\\nWrite the complete app.js file.\"\n    },\n    {\n      \"task_id\": \"integration\",\n      \"description\": \"USER REQUEST: Build a single-page SaaS dashboard landing page with dark/light theme and scroll-triggered section animations. Deliver ONLY: index.html, styles.css, app.js.\\n\\n## 1. THEME SYSTEM (dark mode toggle)\\n- Navbar has a sun/moon emoji button that toggles between dark and light themes\\n- Dark theme: body background #0f172a, text #e2e8f0, cards #1e293b\\n- Light theme: body background #ffffff, text #1e293b, cards #f8fafc\\n- Add a data-theme=\\\"dark\\\" or data-theme=\\\"light\\\" attribute on <html> via JavaScript\\n- Store the user's choice in localStorage; on page reload, restore the saved theme\\n- Default to dark theme on first visit\\n- ALL color changes must use CSS transition: background-color 0.3s, color 0.3s\\n\\n## 2. SCROLL ANIMATIONS (CSS + IntersectionObserver)\\n- Each major <section> starts hidden (opacity: 0, transform: translateY(40px))\\n- When a section scrolls into view (IntersectionObserver at 15% threshold), add class 'visible' which triggers: opacity: 1; transform: translateY(0); transition: all 0.6s ease-out\\n- Sections should animate in staggered \\u2014 each section appears as the user scrolls to it\\n- Hero section animates immediately on page load (no scroll needed)\\n\\n## 3. PAGE SECTIONS (top to bottom)\\n### Navbar (sticky)\\n- Logo text \\\"Dashflow\\\" on the left\\n- 4 nav links: Features, Stats, Pricing, Contact (smooth scroll to section IDs)\\n- Theme toggle button (sun/moon) on the right\\n- Sticks to top when scrolling (position: sticky)\\n\\n### Hero\\n- Large headline \\\"Powerful Analytics for Modern Teams\\\"\\n- Subheadline \\\"Track metrics, gain insights, and grow faster with real-time data.\\\"\\n- CTA button \\\"Get Started Free\\\" with a subtle CSS pulse animation (scale 1->1.03->1 every 2s)\\n- Animated gradient background: linear-gradient that slowly shifts hues using CSS @keyframes\\n\\n### Features (3 cards)\\n- Card 1: icon (bar-chart emoji), title \\\"Real-Time Analytics\\\", description about live dashboards\\n- Card 2: icon (shield emoji), title \\\"Enterprise Security\\\", description about data protection\\n- Card 3: icon (lightning emoji), title \\\"Lightning Fast\\\", description about performance\\n- Cards have hover lift effect: transform: translateY(-4px); box-shadow increase; transition 0.2s\\n\\n### Stats Bar (4 counters)\\n- Projects: 12,500+ \\u2014 Users: 8,200+ \\u2014 Uptime: 99.9% \\u2014 Awards: 24\\n- Each counter animates from 0 to target when the stats section scrolls into view\\n- Use IntersectionObserver + requestAnimationFrame for smooth counting\\n- Numbers should have a subtle scale-pop when reaching their target\\n\\n### Testimonials (carousel)\\n- 3 testimonial cards: quote text, person name, role\\n- Prev/Next buttons and 3 dot indicators below\\n- Clicking a dot or button shows that testimonial with a fade transition\\n- Auto-advance every 5 seconds, but pause when user hovers the carousel\\n\\n### Pricing (3 tiers)\\n- Starter: $9/mo \\u2014 Pro (recommended): $29/mo \\u2014 Enterprise: $99/mo\\n- Pro card should have a highlighted border and \\\"Most Popular\\\" badge\\n- Cards have equal height and center-align\\n- Hover: slight scale(1.02) with box-shadow increase\\n\\n### Newsletter + Footer\\n- Email input + Subscribe button\\n- Validate email format on submit (regex check for @ and .)\\n- Invalid email: show red border + shake animation (CSS @keyframes horizontal shake)\\n- Valid email: clear input, show green \\\"Subscribed!\\\" toast notification that fades out after 3s\\n- Footer: copyright, 3 columns of placeholder links, social media icon placeholders (emoji)\\n\\n## 4. RESPONSIVE DESIGN\\n- Mobile (375px): single column, hamburger menu (animated slide from right), stacked cards\\n- Tablet (768px): 2-column features, stats in 2x2 grid\\n- Desktop (1280px+): 3-column features, stats in a row, full navbar\\n- Use CSS Grid + Flexbox, media queries at 768px and 1024px\\n\\n## 5. CRITICAL RULES\\n- Everything in ONE index.html file with linked styles.css and app.js\\n- ALL CSS classes must have semantic names matching their section (class=\\\"hero\\\", class=\\\"features\\\", class=\\\"stats\\\", class=\\\"testimonials\\\", class=\\\"pricing\\\", class=\\\"newsletter\\\")\\n- JavaScript MUST reference real DOM elements that exist in the HTML\\n- The theme toggle MUST actually change the visual appearance \\u2014 test both themes\\n- Do NOT use any external libraries, CDNs, or frameworks \\u2014 pure HTML/CSS/JS only\\n\\n---\\n\\nIntegration and finalization: You must read all three current files: index.html, styles.css, app.js. Your goal is to ensure that the three files form a completely functional, cohesive single-page application matching the user requirements. Perform the following steps:\\n\\n1. Read index.html and examine its structure, noting all class names, IDs, and data attributes.\\n2. Read styles.css and examine the selectors used. Ensure they match exactly the classes and elements in the HTML. If any discrepancies (e.g., CSS expects a class that HTML doesn't have, or HTML uses a different spelling), fix them by modifying index.html or styles.css accordingly. Pay special attention to responsive classes.\\n3. Read app.js and examine all DOM queries (querySelector, querySelectorAll, getElementById) and event listeners. Verify that every selector corresponds to an element that exists in index.html. If any are missing, either adjust the JS selectors to match the HTML, or add the necessary IDs/classes to index.html.\\n4. Check that the theme system is consistent: the JS sets data-theme on <html>; ensure CSS uses the same attribute selector. Also check that the toggle button emoji changes correctly.\\n5. Verify that the scroll animations are properly wired: the JS adds 'visible' class to sections; CSS defines the transition for that class. Ensure the hero gets 'visible' immediately.\\n6. Ensure the counter animation references match the data-target attributes in the HTML.\\n7. Ensure the carousel HTML structure (cards, dots, prev/next) and JS selectors align.\\n8. Ensure newsletter form has correct input selectors and toast container.\\n9. Add any missing semantic classes or structural adjustments. For example, if the HTML worker omitted a section or used a wrong class, fix it.\\n10. After adjustments, write the final versions of all three files: overwrite index.html, styles.css, app.js with the corrected content. Also add or update any necessary comments or documentation.\\n11. Finally, do a quick read of each file to confirm they are well-formed and complete.\\n\\nYour output should be the final three files. You may modify existing content but must preserve the core functionality.\"\n    },\n    {\n      \"task_id\": \"tester\",\n      \"description\": \"USER REQUEST: Build a single-page SaaS dashboard landing page with dark/light theme and scroll-triggered section animations. Deliver ONLY: index.html, styles.css, app.js.\\n\\n## 1. THEME SYSTEM (dark mode toggle)\\n- Navbar has a sun/moon emoji button that toggles between dark and light themes\\n- Dark theme: body background #0f172a, text #e2e8f0, cards #1e293b\\n- Light theme: body background #ffffff, text #1e293b, cards #f8fafc\\n- Add a data-theme=\\\"dark\\\" or data-theme=\\\"light\\\" attribute on <html> via JavaScript\\n- Store the user's choice in localStorage; on page reload, restore the saved theme\\n- Default to dark theme on first visit\\n- ALL color changes must use CSS transition: background-color 0.3s, color 0.3s\\n\\n## 2. SCROLL ANIMATIONS (CSS + IntersectionObserver)\\n- Each major <section> starts hidden (opacity: 0, transform: translateY(40px))\\n- When a section scrolls into view (IntersectionObserver at 15% threshold), add class 'visible' which triggers: opacity: 1; transform: translateY(0); transition: all 0.6s ease-out\\n- Sections should animate in staggered \\u2014 each section appears as the user scrolls to it\\n- Hero section animates immediately on page load (no scroll needed)\\n\\n## 3. PAGE SECTIONS (top to bottom)\\n### Navbar (sticky)\\n- Logo text \\\"Dashflow\\\" on the left\\n- 4 nav links: Features, Stats, Pricing, Contact (smooth scroll to section IDs)\\n- Theme toggle button (sun/moon) on the right\\n- Sticks to top when scrolling (position: sticky)\\n\\n### Hero\\n- Large headline \\\"Powerful Analytics for Modern Teams\\\"\\n- Subheadline \\\"Track metrics, gain insights, and grow faster with real-time data.\\\"\\n- CTA button \\\"Get Started Free\\\" with a subtle CSS pulse animation (scale 1->1.03->1 every 2s)\\n- Animated gradient background: linear-gradient that slowly shifts hues using CSS @keyframes\\n\\n### Features (3 cards)\\n- Card 1: icon (bar-chart emoji), title \\\"Real-Time Analytics\\\", description about live dashboards\\n- Card 2: icon (shield emoji), title \\\"Enterprise Security\\\", description about data protection\\n- Card 3: icon (lightning emoji), title \\\"Lightning Fast\\\", description about performance\\n- Cards have hover lift effect: transform: translateY(-4px); box-shadow increase; transition 0.2s\\n\\n### Stats Bar (4 counters)\\n- Projects: 12,500+ \\u2014 Users: 8,200+ \\u2014 Uptime: 99.9% \\u2014 Awards: 24\\n- Each counter animates from 0 to target when the stats section scrolls into view\\n- Use IntersectionObserver + requestAnimationFrame for smooth counting\\n- Numbers should have a subtle scale-pop when reaching their target\\n\\n### Testimonials (carousel)\\n- 3 testimonial cards: quote text, person name, role\\n- Prev/Next buttons and 3 dot indicators below\\n- Clicking a dot or button shows that testimonial with a fade transition\\n- Auto-advance every 5 seconds, but pause when